,Recommended,497180,29325099,Posted: 17 January,all,Eclipse,"The game is quite old. It was released in 2003 by Invictus Games. Invictus Games finally named it abandonedware and moved on. Imagecode managed to revive the game and put it on steam. Even till this day, They slowly update this game. What makes it unique is that this is a game using an engine from the late 1990s and was released in 2003, but is still being updated as of 2017.The game is quite fun with tons of tuning and racing. You can tune up a car and take it to a street race, drag race, or another racing event. Career mode can be challenging as you have little funds to buy a functioning car and start racing. If you accidentally crash, the effects can be devastating. You will lose parts and your chassis will become mangled up. And worse yet, crash damage is permanent unless repaired with money. Once you get enough cash and a good car, you can fine-tune your car and decorate it with your heart's desire.The game also uses workshop integration as well as having a large modding community online. There are thousands of mods that add cosmetics, performance parts, cars, and even new tracks.Sadly, the game is NOT stable. Crashes are more than common and can lead to deletion of progress. Every button click makes you cross your fingers in hope that the game wont crash. But luckily, the game is still being updated and patches are still rolling out.Pros:+Classic+Still indev+Indepth tuning+Racing+Challenging+Workshop integration and mods.Cons:-Unstable9/10"
