76561198341704663,Recommended,497180,28580986,"Posted: 23 December, 2016",all,Lil Pump,"I've just started to get the hang of the game, pretty entertaining so far. A bit tough to figure out in the beginning due there being no tutorial, but after that it's cool to be able to customize so many parts of the car in great detail. Only problem so far was the second time I opened the game, the resolution got set to minimum and the text was giant and almost impossible to press. If this happens to you, just try to go to the settings and reset the resolution and then restart the game. Game may be a bit buggy and tough to figure out, but I have a feeling I'll be enjoying it in the future.(Edit)4 hours or so after downloading the game, I tried to launch it again, this time with a mod car installed. The game now crashes whenever I try to enter a race or the free roam area. Not sure if the crashing is directly correlated with installing mods, but there is a chance. Changing my review to not recommended due to this. Hopefully this might get fixed in a future update.(Edit #2)I looked at the error.log (don't know why I didn't do so earlier) and I saw the game was attempting to call a class file from a mod I had deleted. Since the file was deleted, the game would crash. I did a clean install of the game and was able to get it working again. Game works great just as I stated originally, but I would not recommend installing mods due to problems like this."
