,Recommended,497180,34150234,Posted: 10 August,all,Fetus Deletus,"I remember playing the first Street Legal years ago, and when I saw this game for 6 bucks in early January, couldn't buy it fast enough. Played it for the first ten hours, resisting the mod-bug, until I finally snapped and spend several hours browsing Vstanced and other sites looking for vehicle and engine mods. After those several hours, it crashes lots, and especially on the chassis menu (mod's fault, not game problem). The devs have been putting in work on getting the game stable since it dropped on steam, huge applause to them.PROS:can run on literally ♥♥♥♥ing any computer from 2003 onwards: very, very low requirementsHUGE modding support from both external websites and steam workshopVery fun to waste an hour building a car, then crashing into a wall and losing the engine. (this will happen a lot)Cheats make the game's grind magically disappear.Good soundtrack for it's time, along with it's graphics (which can be improved with mods)AMAZING variety of cars even in the base game, with each car model coming with at least 2 variations of it, with high-performance models or topless variants.Can call police fat to their face.Game is decently challenging without cheats.Engines are amazingly customizable, like choosing between nitro meth or pump fuel, going NA or turbo, what drive you want the car in (FR, FF, AWD).CONS:Crashes. And freezing.Go onto a curb with lowered suspension and lose your front bumper.Engines have wings. (crash into anything at 50+ mph and it flies out. (this can possibly be rectified in the game's settings, there is a slider to tone down or up the destruction to cars, I personally haven't touched it.)The graphics (game is from 2003)Soundtrack can get repetitive (What about the forest? Nope.)Mods can affect the game drastically depending on what you install, keep track of what you install; test the game before and after installing one.TL;DR, get the game, pretty good for it's price and its fun to waste time on."
